<dd  class="accordion-def"><img alt="Board Member Steven Lowy, 2019 Winners Nick McKenzie and Sashka Koloff, Media Award Lecturer Ita Buttrose, Chair of ABC" data-align="center" data-caption="Board Member Steven Lowy, 2019 Winners Nick McKenzie and Sashka Koloff, Media Award Lecturer Ita Buttrose, Chair of ABC" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="1bdd60fc-c2a7-4052-a715-8998f83f4276" src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/LIMA-2019-Award-Winners-Nick-Mckenzie-Sashka-Koloff.jpg" />
<p><iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="320" scrolling="no" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/bK6PRkPyf5c" width="600"></iframe></p>

<p>The winners of the 2019 Media Award were Nick McKenzie and Sashka Koloff for their&nbsp;<em>Four Corners</em>&nbsp;episode ‘Interference’ - a joint investigation with ABC,&nbsp;<em>The Sydney Morning Herald</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>The Age.</em>&nbsp;The episode looks at China's covert political influence campaign in Australia.</p>

<p>They were awarded a cash prize of $20,000 as well as the Lowy Institute Media Award trophy, created by Dinosaur Designs.</p>

<p>The other finalists were:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Matthew Carney</strong>&nbsp;– nominated for “Leave No Dark Corner” – an episode on ABC’s Foreign Correspondent about China’s social credit system;</li>
<li><strong>Kate Geraghty</strong>&nbsp;– nominated for a selection of photography in The Sydney Morning Herald and The Age; and</li>
<li><strong>Angus Grigg, Lisa Murray, Jonathan Shapiro and Edmund Tadros</strong>&nbsp;– nominated for a series of articles on the security firm Paladin in the Australian Financial Review.</li>
</ul>

<p>The 2019 Media Lecturer was Ita Buttrose AC OBE, Chair of the ABC.</p>

<p>We are pleased to recognise Rio Tinto’s sponsorship of the 2019 Lowy Institute Media Award Dinner.</p>

